Function Reference/the author nickname « WordPress Codex
-----------

This tag displays the nickname for the author of a post. The
**Nickname** field is set in the user's profile
([Administration](/Administration_Panels "Administration Panels") \>
[Profile](/Administration_Panels#Your_Profile "Administration Panels")
\> [Your Profile](/Your_Profile_SubPanel "Your Profile SubPanel")). This
tag must be used within [The Loop](/The_Loop "The Loop").

Replace With
------------

-   [the\_author\_meta('nickname')](/Template_Tags/the_author_meta "Template Tags/the author meta")

Usage
-----

`  <?php the_author_nickname(); ?> `

Parameters
----------

This tag does not accept any parameters.

Example
-------

    <p>Posted by <?php the_author_nickname(); ?></p>

Change Log
----------

-   Since: 1.5.0
-   Deprecated: 2.8.0
-   Replace By:
    [the\_author\_meta('nickname')](/Template_Tags/the_author_meta "Template Tags/the author meta")

